      <div class="legal__body">
        <h2>1. How Moose works</h2>
        <p>
          This section is included as a general overview of how Moose works. The operative
          provisions of these Terms prevail to the extent of any inconsistency.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Moose enables fitness studios to form direct cross-venue access partnerships with other Participating Studios.</li>
          <li>A Studio can use Moose to partner with other studios, so that its Eligible Members can add the Moose Upgrade and access Crossover Sessions at those Partner Studios.</li>
          <li>The Studios decide which Partnerships they wish to establish through Moose.</li>
          <li>Once the Studio has at least one live Partnership through Moose, the Studio may make the Moose Upgrade available to Eligible Members.</li>
          <li>The Moose Upgrade is connected to the Moose User's Home Studio and operates as an add-on to the Moose User's Eligible membership product with that Home Studio.</li>
          <li>A Moose User is entitled to access Crossover Sessions at their Home Studio's Partner Studios which are in place from time to time, and may also receive access to other features, benefits, content, offers, services or functionality made available through Moose.</li>
          <li>Unless otherwise agreed between the parties, the Studio collects Upgrade Fees from Moose Users on Moose's behalf in accordance with these Terms.</li>
          <li>Moose Users are subject to the Moose User Terms. The Moose User Terms require Moose Users to comply with the applicable terms, rules, policies, waivers and reasonable directions of any Partner Studio they attend through Moose.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Moose Upgrades</h2>
        <p>
          The below table sets out the Moose Upgrades which are available for the Studio to offer to
          its Members. These may depend on the nature of the Partnership the Studio enters into with a
          Partner Studio, which is handled within the Platform.
        </p>
        <p>This list may change from time to time and will be reflected in the Platform.</p>

        <div class="legal__table-wrap">
          <table class="legal__table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th rowspan="2" scope="col">Moose Upgrade</th>
                <th colspan="3" scope="colgroup">Crossover Sessions</th>
                <th colspan="2" scope="colgroup">Partnership</th>
                <th colspan="3" scope="colgroup">Fees</th>
                <th colspan="3" scope="colgroup">Fee Split</th>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Reference</th>
                <th scope="col">Credits Per Cycle</th>
                <th scope="col">Cycle</th>
                <th scope="col">Partnership Basis</th>
                <th scope="col">Peak Class Capacity</th>
                <th scope="col">Weekly Fee</th>
                <th scope="col">Fortnightly Fee</th>
                <th scope="col">Monthly Fee</th>
                <th scope="col">Moose Portion</th>
                <th scope="col">Home Studio Portion</th>
                <th scope="col">Pooled Portion</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td colspan="12" class="legal__table-note">Current Moose Upgrade values are shown in the Platform.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>All fees shown include GST.</p>
        <p>
          Where the Studio has multiple live Partnerships and more than one Moose Upgrade could apply,
          the applicable Moose Upgrade will be the Moose Upgrade with the highest Weekly Upgrade Fee
          that is applicable to any live Partnership involving the Studio.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Exclusivity</h2>
        <p>
          While the Studio is Active, the Studio must not participate in, promote, integrate with,
          refer Members or Moose Users to, or otherwise support a Copycat Competitor.
        </p>
        <p>The restriction in this section continues for 12 months after the later of:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>the end of the Studio's last live Partnership; and</li>
          <li>the last date on which a Moose User Connected to the Studio held or used the Moose Upgrade.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          For clarity, this section does not restrict the Studio from participating in consumer-facing
          fitness marketplaces, aggregators or lead-generation platforms that are not Copycat
          Competitors.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By creating a Studio Account, accessing or using Moose, making the Moose Upgrade available to
          Members, forming or participating in a Partnership, or otherwise participating in Moose, the
          Studio accepts and agrees to be bound by these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Participation in Moose</h2>
        <p>
          Subject to these Terms, Moose permits the Studio to participate in Moose, access and use the
          Platform, form Partnerships, and make the Moose Upgrade available to Eligible Members while
          the Studio is Active.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Moose Upgrade and Moose Users</h2>
        <p>
          The Studio may determine which of its membership products are Eligible. Moose may reject,
          remove or disable eligibility for any membership product where Moose reasonably considers
          that membership product is inappropriate, incompatible with Moose, inconsistent with the
          intended operation of the Moose Upgrade, or otherwise unsuitable for participation in Moose.
          Moose will notify the Studio if Moose rejects, removes or disables eligibility for a
          membership product.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Moose User Terms will require Moose Users to comply with the applicable terms,
          conditions, rules, policies, waivers and reasonable directions of any Partner Studio they
          attend or seek to attend through Moose.
        </p>
        <p>
          Moose may make additional features, benefits, content, offers, services or functionality
          available to Moose Users from time to time. Moose may determine, vary, restrict, suspend or
          remove those features, benefits, content, offers, services or functionality through the
          Platform.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Studio must ensure that Moose has access to accurate and current information, whether
          through the Platform or otherwise, about whether each Moose User Connected to the Studio
          continues to hold an Eligible membership product with the Studio. The Studio must not
          withhold, obscure, disable, manipulate or otherwise interfere with Moose's access to that
          information.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Partnerships</h2>
        <p>
          The Studio may form one or more Partnerships with other Participating Studios through the
          Platform, or as otherwise enabled by Moose.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each Partnership requires the consent of the Participating Studios involved and is subject to
          the Platform requirements. Moose may refuse, suspend or disable a Partnership where Moose
          reasonably considers it necessary to protect Moose, Moose Users, Participating Studios, the
          Platform or the proper operation of the network.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Studio must give the relevant Partner Studio at least 90 days' notice, through the
          Platform or in writing, to end a Partnership, unless the Studio and the relevant Partner
          Studio agree to end the Partnership earlier.
        </p>
        <p>
          Where a Partner Studio considers that the other Partner Studio is in material breach of the
          Studio Conduct Policy and wishes to end the Partnership earlier, that Partner Studio must
          notify Moose. Moose may then suspend, restrict or end the Partnership where Moose considers
          it appropriate in accordance with these Terms.
        </p>
        <p>Each Partnership is subject to the <a href="/studio-conduct">Studio Conduct Policy</a>.</p>

        <h2>8. Partnership Formats</h2>
        <p>Moose may make different formats of Partnerships available through the Platform from time to time.</p>
        <p>These may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Open Partnerships</strong> — where Moose Users may access Crossover Sessions at a Partner Studio without Peak Class capacity restrictions.</li>
          <li><strong>Peak-Limited Partnerships</strong> — where the number of Moose Users who may book or attend Peak Classes is limited to the applicable Peak Class Capacity.</li>
          <li><strong>Off-Peak Partnerships</strong> — where Moose Users are not permitted to book or attend Peak Classes.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The Moose Partnership Formats made available through Moose are subject to change and may be
          added to, removed, renamed, replaced or varied by Moose from time to time.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Staff Crossover Access</h2>
        <p>
          The Studio and a Partner Studio may agree through the Platform whether their respective
          Studio Personnel may access Crossover Sessions or other services at each other's venues
          through Moose without paying an Upgrade Fee.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unless otherwise agreed by Moose, Staff Crossover Access does not create any entitlement to a
          Moose Upgrade, does not require payment of an Upgrade Fee, and does not give rise to any Moose
          Portion, Home Studio Portion or Pooled Portion.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Studio obligations</h2>
        <p>The Studio must:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>participate in Moose in good faith;</li>
          <li>comply with these Terms, the Studio Conduct Policy, the Promotional Playbook and the way the Platform is configured, operated and made available by Moose;</li>
          <li>ensure its Studio Personnel comply with these Terms, the Studio Conduct Policy and the way the Platform is configured, operated and made available by Moose, to the extent applicable to them;</li>
          <li>keep its class, capacity, schedule, attendance, membership and billing information accurate and up to date;</li>
          <li>honour valid Crossover Session bookings made through Moose, subject to these Terms, the Studio Conduct Policy and the way the Platform is configured, operated and made available by Moose;</li>
          <li>operate its venue, classes, facilities and services safely and lawfully;</li>
          <li>hold and maintain all licences, permits, approvals, registrations and authorisations required to operate its venue and provide its classes, facilities and services;</li>
          <li>cooperate reasonably with Moose in connection with Moose Users, Visiting Users, payments, reconciliation, incidents, integrations, Crossover Sessions and Partnerships; and</li>
          <li>not misuse Moose data, Platform data, Member data, Moose User data, Visiting User data or information relating to any Participating Studio.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. Upgrade Fees and commercial allocation</h2>
        <p>Moose may introduce, vary, replace, remove or update Commercial Terms in accordance with these Terms.</p>
        <p>Moose will give the Studio at least 90 days' notice before any change to the Commercial Terms takes effect for the Studio.</p>
        <p>
          Moose may determine how and when changes to the Commercial Terms apply to existing and future
          Moose Users, provided Moose has given any required notice under these Terms.
        </p>
        <p>
          Moose may introduce new optional Moose Upgrades, partnership structures, access options or
          commercial options at any time. If a new option is optional and does not alter the Studio's
          existing Commercial Terms unless adopted, Moose is not required to give 90 days' notice
          before making it available.
        </p>
        <p>
          Percentages are calculated by reference to the Upgrade Fee actually collected, subject to
          promotions, discounts, failed payments, chargebacks and other adjustments.
        </p>
        <p>The Moose Portion is retained by Moose.</p>
        <p>The Home Studio Portion is the portion payable or credited to the Home Studio.</p>
        <p>
          The Pooled Portion is administered by Moose and distributed to Participating Studios as
          determined by Moose from time to time. Moose does not retain any part of the Pooled Portion.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Studio may determine the billing frequency, billing cycle and billing arrangements for
          collecting Upgrade Fees from Moose Users, including applying different billing arrangements
          to different Moose Users.
        </p>
        <p>
          Where the Studio charges Moose Users weekly, fortnightly or monthly, the Studio must charge
          the applicable Weekly Upgrade Fee, Fortnightly Upgrade Fee or Monthly Upgrade Fee specified
          in the Moose Upgrades section. Where the Studio charges or packages the Moose Upgrade on any
          other basis, the applicable Upgrade Fee will be as otherwise provided by Moose.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Collection of Upgrade Fees</h2>
        <p>The Studio collects Upgrade Fees from Moose Users for and on behalf of Moose, unless Moose agrees or provides otherwise.</p>
        <p>
          Upgrade Fees are Moose's revenue and not the Studio's revenue, except to the extent of any
          Home Studio Portion or Pooled Portion payable or credited to the Studio under these Terms.
        </p>
        <p>The Studio must hold and account to Moose for all Upgrade Fees it collects in accordance with these Terms and the reconciliation process.</p>
        <p>The Studio must not deduct, withhold, set off or apply any amount from Upgrade Fees except as expressly permitted by Moose or these Terms.</p>
        <p>Merchant, gateway, processing and other transaction fees incurred in collecting Upgrade Fees are borne by the Studio unless Moose agrees otherwise.</p>
        <p>
          The Studio must ensure that Moose has access to accurate and complete information, whether
          through the Platform or otherwise, about all Upgrade Fees charged to, collected from,
          refunded to, discounted for, reversed for, failed for, charged back for or otherwise adjusted
          in respect of Moose Users Connected to the Studio. The Studio must not withhold, obscure,
          disable, manipulate or otherwise interfere with Moose's access to that information.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Reconciliation</h2>
        <p>Moose will reconcile Upgrade Fees at approximately 90-day intervals, or at any other interval notified by Moose in accordance with these Terms.</p>
        <p>
          As part of each reconciliation, Moose may calculate all Upgrade Fees collected, Moose
          Portions, Home Studio Portions, Pooled Portion distributions, refunds, discounts, failed
          payments, chargebacks and other adjustments.
        </p>
        <p>Moose may set off amounts owing between Moose and the Studio. Only the resulting net amount is payable by one party to the other.</p>
        <p>Moose may issue a reconciliation statement, and the relevant party must pay any net amount owing within the period specified by Moose.</p>

        <h2>14. Direct debit</h2>
        <p>Moose may require the Studio to provide and maintain a valid direct debit authority or other payment authority.</p>
        <p>Moose may debit weekly, fortnightly, monthly or other estimated amounts on account of amounts Moose reasonably estimates will be payable by the Studio at the next reconciliation.</p>
        <p>All debited amounts will be credited against the next reconciliation.</p>
        <p>The Studio must promptly remedy any failed debit or unpaid amount.</p>

        <h2>15. GST</h2>
        <p>Unless stated otherwise, amounts payable under these Terms are GST-inclusive where payable by Members or Moose Users, and otherwise are treated in accordance with GST Law.</p>
        <p>Each party is responsible for complying with its own GST obligations.</p>
        <p>
          Moose may issue or control receipts, tax invoices, adjustment notes, reconciliation
          statements and other payment records relating to the Moose Upgrade, and may amend invoicing,
          payment or reconciliation processes where reasonably required for GST, tax, accounting or
          compliance purposes.
        </p>

        <h2>16. Promotional Playbook</h2>
        <p>The Promotional Playbook sets out the agreed activities the parties will carry out to support awareness and promotion of Moose.</p>
        <p>The Studio must comply with the Promotional Playbook.</p>
        <p>Moose may update the Promotional Playbook from time to time. Any updated Promotional Playbook applies to the Studio once published, made available or provided by Moose.</p>
        <p>The Studio may request changes to its Promotional Playbook obligations, with any agreed changes to be recorded or confirmed by Moose.</p>

        <h2>17. Studio Conduct Policy</h2>
        <p>
          The <a href="/studio-conduct">Studio Conduct Policy</a> sets out the baseline conduct rules,
          expectations and obligations that apply to Participating Studios, Partnerships and
          interactions between Participating Studios, Partner Studios, Members, Moose Users and Visiting
          Users.
        </p>
        <p>The Studio must comply with the Studio Conduct Policy.</p>
        <p>
          Partner Studios are also required to comply with the Studio Conduct Policy under their own
          participation arrangements with Moose, so the Studio can expect the same baseline conduct
          rules, expectations and obligations to apply to each Partner Studio it partners with through
          Moose.
        </p>
        <p>Moose may update the Studio Conduct Policy from time to time. Any updated Studio Conduct Policy applies to the Studio once published, made available or provided by Moose.</p>
        <p>If Moose, the Studio or a Partner Studio considers that another Participating Studio has breached the Studio Conduct Policy in connection with a Partnership, the issue may be notified to Moose and/or the relevant Participating Studio.</p>
        <p>For non-urgent breaches that are capable of remedy, the relevant Participating Studio must be given a reasonable opportunity to remedy the breach before Moose takes action in respect of that breach.</p>
        <p>
          Moose may take immediate action, and a Studio may request immediate action by Moose, without
          first giving the relevant Participating Studio an opportunity to remedy where Moose reasonably
          considers that the breach is material, not capable of remedy, requires immediate resolution,
          or immediate action is necessary to protect Moose, Moose Users, Members, Participating
          Studios, the Platform, safety, legal compliance, payment integrity, data integrity, member
          experience or the proper operation of Moose.
        </p>
        <p>
          Where Moose is entitled to take action in respect of a Studio Conduct Policy breach, Moose
          may suspend or restrict a Studio's access to Moose, suspend or end any Partnership involving
          that Studio, restrict that Studio's ability to offer or accept Crossover Sessions, suspend or
          remove Moose Users' access through that Studio, or terminate that Studio's participation in
          Moose.
        </p>

        <h2>18. Publicity</h2>
        <p>Moose may publicly identify the Studio as participating in Moose for Moose's promotional purposes.</p>

        <h2>19. Promotions and discounts</h2>
        <p>
          Moose may, acting reasonably, offer referral incentives or other promotional offers in
          relation to the Moose Upgrade, provided that Moose must not apply any such offer in a way that
          deliberately and unfairly prejudices the Studio.
        </p>
        <p>Moose may determine how any Moose-applied or Moose-approved referral incentive or promotional offer is treated for the purposes of calculating the Moose Portion, Home Studio Portion and Pooled Portion.</p>
        <p>
          The Studio may offer the Moose Upgrade to a Moose User at a price lower than the applicable
          Upgrade Fee. If it does so, unless Moose agrees otherwise, the Moose Portion and Pooled
          Portion will still be calculated as if the full applicable Upgrade Fee had been collected.
        </p>

        <h2>20. Platform control</h2>
        <p>
          Moose may determine, configure, apply, vary, restrict, suspend, disable or otherwise control
          the setup, operation, functionality, availability and use of the Platform from time to time,
          including how Moose Upgrades, Partnerships, Crossover Sessions and access rights are enabled,
          managed or restricted through the Platform. The Studio must comply with, and give effect to,
          the way the Platform is configured, operated and made available by Moose.
        </p>

        <h2>21. Intellectual property and data</h2>
        <p>Moose owns all rights in the Platform, Moose brand, Moose materials, Platform data, usage data and analytics generated through Moose.</p>
        <p>The Studio may use Moose's name, materials and Platform only as permitted by Moose and only for the purposes of participating in Moose.</p>
        <p>The Studio grants Moose the right to use information, data and materials provided or made available by the Studio for operating, administering, improving, analysing and promoting Moose, subject to applicable privacy laws.</p>
        <p>Moose may use aggregated, anonymised or de-identified data and insights generated through Moose for analytics, benchmarking, reporting, product development, investor materials, commercial analysis, marketing and other business purposes.</p>

        <h2>22. Confidentiality and privacy</h2>
        <p>Each party must keep the other party's confidential information confidential and use it only for the purposes of these Terms, except where disclosure is required by law or to professional advisers.</p>
        <p>The Studio must not use Moose data, Member data, Moose User data, Visiting User data, Platform information, pricing, usage information or information relating to any Participating Studio except as permitted by Moose and for the purposes of participating in Moose.</p>
        <p>Each party must comply with applicable privacy laws, and the Studio must promptly notify Moose of any actual or suspected data breach, privacy issue or unauthorised use of Moose data, Member data, Moose User data, Visiting User data or Platform information.</p>

        <h2>23. Liability and indemnity</h2>
        <p>Moose does not own, operate or control the Studio's venue, classes, instructors, staff, equipment, facilities or services. The Studio is solely responsible for the operation, safety, quality and compliance of its venue, classes, instructors, staff, equipment, facilities and services.</p>
        <p>Moose does not own, operate or control any Partner Studio's venue, classes, instructors, staff, equipment, facilities or services. Moose is not responsible for any act, omission, conduct, service failure, injury, incident, loss, damage or claim arising from or connected with a Partner Studio, its venue, classes, instructors, staff, equipment, facilities or services.</p>
        <p>The Studio indemnifies Moose against any loss, claim, liability, damage, cost or expense arising out of or in connection with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>the Studio's venue, classes, instructors, staff, equipment, facilities or services;</li>
          <li>the Studio's breach of law, negligence, misconduct or breach of these Terms;</li>
          <li>the Studio's misuse of data, Platform information, Member data, Moose User data, Visiting User data or information relating to any Participating Studio; or</li>
          <li>any claim by a Member, Moose User, Visiting User, Studio Personnel or other person relating to the Studio, its venue, classes, instructors, staff, equipment, facilities or services.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Moose's aggregate liability under or in connection with these Terms is capped at the total Moose Portion retained by Moose in respect of Moose Users Connected to the Studio during the 36 months before the event giving rise to the liability.</p>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Moose is not liable for indirect, consequential, special or punitive loss, loss of profit, loss of revenue, loss of goodwill, loss of opportunity or loss of anticipated savings.</p>
        <p>Nothing in these Terms excludes, restricts or modifies any right, remedy, guarantee or obligation that cannot be excluded, restricted or modified by law.</p>

        <h2>24. Insurance</h2>
        <p>The Studio must hold and maintain, with reputable insurers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>public liability insurance of not less than $20 million per occurrence;</li>
          <li>any professional indemnity, instructor, personal training, participant accident, member injury or similar insurance appropriate to the Studio's activities, disciplines, facilities and services; and</li>
          <li>workers compensation insurance and any other insurance required by law.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The Studio must ensure it holds insurance that is appropriate to cover claims, accidents, injuries, incidents or losses involving Members, Moose Users, Visiting Users, Studio Personnel and other persons attending or using the Studio's venue, classes, facilities or services.</p>
        <p>The Studio must provide Moose with certificates of currency or other evidence of insurance on request.</p>

        <h2>25. Suspension</h2>
        <p>Moose may suspend or restrict the Studio's access to the Platform, the Studio's ability to offer or accept Crossover Sessions, or any Moose User's access through the Studio, where Moose reasonably considers it necessary to protect Moose, Moose Users, Members, Participating Studios, the Platform, safety, legal compliance, payment integrity, data integrity, member experience or the proper operation of Moose.</p>

        <h2>26. Continuing application, cancellation and termination</h2>
        <p>The Studio may stop participating in Moose by ceasing to use the Platform, ending its live Partnerships, stopping the offer of new Moose Upgrades and, where applicable, closing or deactivating its Studio Account.</p>
        <p>The Studio must continue to comply with these Terms while:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>any Partnership involving the Studio remains live;</li>
          <li>any Moose Upgrade made available through the Studio remains active, on foot or has not yet expired;</li>
          <li>any Moose User Connected to the Studio continues to have access to Moose, Crossover Sessions or other benefits through the Moose Upgrade;</li>
          <li>any notice period required to end a Partnership is still running;</li>
          <li>any amount remains owing under these Terms;</li>
          <li>any reconciliation obligation remains outstanding; or</li>
          <li>any other continuing obligation under these Terms remains applicable.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>If the Studio stops participating in Moose or ceases to have any live Partnerships, the Moose Upgrade for Moose Users Connected to the Studio will ordinarily continue until the end of the applicable billing cycle. Moose may, acting reasonably, determine that the Moose Upgrade ends, suspends or transitions earlier or otherwise where necessary, including because of breach, safety, compliance, payment, technical, integration, platform integrity, member experience or urgent operational reasons.</p>
        <p>Moose may suspend, restrict or terminate the Studio's access to Moose, including the Studio Account, where permitted under these Terms.</p>
        <p>Stopping participation in Moose does not affect any accrued rights or obligations, any amounts owing, any reconciliation obligations, or any clauses that are intended to continue after participation ends.</p>
        <p>If the Studio later resumes access to or use of Moose, forms a new Partnership, or makes the Moose Upgrade available again, these Terms will apply without requiring the parties to enter into a new agreement.</p>

        <h2>27. Dispute resolution</h2>
        <p>Before starting court proceedings, a party must notify the other party of the dispute and the parties must use reasonable endeavours to resolve it promptly. This does not prevent either party from seeking urgent injunctive, interlocutory or equitable relief.</p>

        <h2>28. General</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of New South Wales, Australia.</p>
        <p>The Studio must not assign, transfer or otherwise deal with its rights or obligations under these Terms without Moose's prior written consent.</p>
        <p>Moose may assign, transfer or otherwise deal with its rights or obligations under these Terms as part of a restructure, sale, merger, financing, change of control, transfer of business or other corporate transaction.</p>
        <p>If any part of these Terms is invalid, unenforceable or unlawful, that part is to be read down or severed to the extent necessary, and the remaining parts continue in full force.</p>
        <p>If the 12-month period in the Exclusivity section is invalid, unenforceable or unlawful, that period is to be read down so that the restriction applies for the longest shorter period permitted by law.</p>
        <p>No failure or delay by Moose in exercising any right, power or remedy under these Terms is a waiver of that right, power or remedy.</p>
        <p>These Terms, together with the Studio Conduct Policy, Promotional Playbook, Moose User Terms and any other document, policy or requirement referred to in these Terms, set out the terms that apply to the Studio's participation in Moose.</p>
        <p>A Partnership is a platform and commercial arrangement only. The term "Partnership" is used in these Terms to describe the commercial arrangement between Participating Studios through Moose, and does not create a legal partnership, joint venture, franchise, employment, agency or fiduciary relationship between Moose, the Studio or any Participating Studio.</p>
        <p>Moose may give notices, updates or communications to the Studio through the Platform, by email, by making them available through Moose, or by any other method Moose reasonably considers appropriate.</p>

        <h2>29. Definitions</h2>
        <dl class="legal__defs">
          <dt>Active</dt>
          <dd>means in respect of the Studio, that the Studio has at least one live Partnership through Moose.</dd>

          <dt>ClassPass</dt>
          <dd>means the business operated under the ClassPass name or brand.</dd>

          <dt>Copycat Competitor</dt>
          <dd>means any platform, software, service, arrangement or business model that enables fitness studios, gyms or similar venues to participate in reciprocal member-sharing arrangements with each other, where members of one participating venue are given access to classes, sessions or services at another participating venue because of a reciprocal relationship, partnership or arrangement between those specific venues. For clarity, consumer-facing fitness marketplaces, aggregators or lead-generation platforms are not Copycat Competitors to the extent they operate primarily by giving consumers access to a broader network of venues through the marketplace, aggregator or lead-generation model, rather than by facilitating reciprocal member-sharing arrangements between specific participating venues. ClassPass' core and traditional business model is an example of this type of consumer-facing marketplace or aggregator model.</dd>

